5|$|The {{council is}} based in the Civic Offices, which house {{departments}} such as tax support, <b>housing</b> <b>benefits,</b> resident services, and municipal functions. They are situated in Guildhall Square, along with Portsmouth Guildhall and Portsmouth Central Library. The Guildhall {{is a symbol of}} Portsmouth, serving principally as a cultural venue. It was designed by Leeds-based architect William Hill, who first started constructing it in the neo-classical style in 1873 at the cost of £140,000. The Guildhall was opened to the public in 1890.|$|E
