40|$|This report {{presents}} {{findings of}} qualitative {{research into the}} procedures used to verify <b>Housing</b> <b>Benefit</b> and Council Tax Benefit claims in {{a representative sample of}} 30 local authorities. It includes information on local authorities' approach to fraud prevention, application forms, internal auditing and the resource implications of setting up and operating the Department's forthcoming Verification Framework for <b>Housing</b> <b>Benefit</b> and Council Tax Benefit claims. The research was based on interviews with <b>Housing</b> <b>Benefit</b> Managers, front-line staff, internal auditors and fraud officers in each local authority...|$|R
